Emergency Mode Sequence — GEMS

Activation Logic for Crisis Oxygen Generation

This flowchart shows how GEMS transitions from long-term dormancy into operational emergency mode.
It outlines trigger conditions, system checks, activation stages, and final O₂ delivery behavior.

This sequence is intentionally simple — GEMS avoids complex logic or heavy processing to maximize reliability after years of inactivity.

Primary Trigger Conditions

GEMS activates when at least one of the following occurs:

Catastrophic primary oxygen system failure

Rapid depressurization event

Habitat O₂ partial pressure drops below safe threshold

Power-grid loss prevents primary ISRU from operating

Manual emergency activation by crew

ACS-2 Emergency Mode Sequence Diagram
                        ┌──────────────────────────┐
                        │   START: Dormant State   │
                        │ (Years of inactivity)    │
                        └─────────────┬────────────┘
                                      │
                                      ▼
                    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐
                    │ Detect Emergency Condition        │
                    │ - Low O₂                         │
                    │ - Pressure loss                  │
                    │ - Power failure                  │
                    │ - Manual command                 │
                    └─────────────┬────────────────────┘
                                  │
                                  ▼
                    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐
                    │ Integrity Self-Check              │
                    │ - Thermal status valid            │
                    │ - No mechanical obstruction       │
                    │ - Actuator readiness              │
                    └─────────────┬────────────────────┘
                                  │
                    ┌─────────────┴──────────────┐
                    │                            │
                    ▼                            ▼
        ┌───────────────────┐         ┌────────────────────────┐
        │  FAIL CONDITION   │         │      PASS CONDITION    │
        │  → Safe Standby   │         │ → Proceed to Activation│
        └───────┬───────────┘         └───────────┬────────────┘
                │                                 │
                ▼                                 ▼
        (System halts until             ┌─────────────────────────┐
         conditions stabilize)          │ Processing Core Warm-Up │
                                        │ Slow rise → avoid shock │
                                        └───────────┬────────────┘
                                                    │
                                                    ▼
                                  ┌────────────────────────────────┐
                                  │ Begin Oxygen Generation         │
                                  │ - Controlled heat application   │
                                  │ - O₂-bearing gas produced       │
                                  └─────────────┬──────────────────┘
                                                │
                                                ▼
                          ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
                          │ Gas Routing Path                       │
                          │ Isolation Gate → Buffer → Regulator    │
                          └─────────────┬──────────────────────────┘
                                        │
                                        ▼
                     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
                     │ Deliver Oxygen to Habitat Systems           │
                     │ - Pressure stabilization                    │
                     │ - EVA shelter supply                        │
                     │ - Emergency breathing atmosphere            │
                     └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

